@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{org-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in Org mode with a substantial
collection of commands and helper functions that address gaps in
day-to-day Org workflows.  Where Org mode provides the foundation for
outlining, task management, clocking, and document authoring,
@samp{org-extras.el} adds convenience commands, DWIM behaviors, and
integration glue that make those workflows smoother and more
keyboard-driven.

The package depends on @samp{el-patch} (for patching several upstream Org
functions), @samp{paths} (for resolving common directory and file paths), and
@samp{transient} (for the navigation menus).  Several commands also rely on
external tools such as @samp{org-roam}, @samp{pandoc}, @samp{pngpaste}, and @samp{gdrive}.

The extensions can be grouped into several thematic areas:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Editing and navigation.}  Commands for copying heading names and
contents, inserting subheadings, counting words, extracting and
manipulating links, pasting clipboard content as Org markup or images,
and toggling inline image display (@ref{Editing and navigation}).

@item
@strong{Agenda management.}  Commands for switching to the daily agenda view,
clocking in from the agenda, marking items done or postponed, toggling
anniversary display, and DWIM switching between agenda log lines and
source files (@ref{Agenda management}).

@item
@strong{Clocking and timestamps.}  Commands for inserting clock entries and
timestamps, jumping to the latest clock entry, inserting clock
reports, sorting clock tables, deleting headings without logbooks, and
automatically adding meeting participants when clocking in
(@ref{Clocking and timestamps}).

@item
@strong{Capture hooks.}  A comprehensive hook function that performs
context-dependent actions when finalizing Org capture templates
(@ref{Capture hook function, , Capture hooks}).

@item
@strong{Folding, cycling, and narrowing.}  Enhanced global cycling that hides
archives, commands to show properties and logbooks, and narrowing
commands that respect subtree structure (@ref{Folding cycling and narrowing, , Folding@comma{} cycling@comma{} and narrowing}).

@item
@strong{ID management.}  Automatic addition of Org IDs to headings with
fine-grained exclusion controls, updating ID locations across the Org
directory, and a workflow for finding and resolving duplicate IDs
(@ref{ID management}).

@item
@strong{Refiling.}  Commands for jumping to the last refiled item, refiling
and archiving in a single step, refiling to specific positions, and
regenerating the refile cache (@ref{Refiling}).

@item
@strong{Links and sorting.}  Sorting lists of Org links, linkifying plain
text against Org Roam nodes, and copying EWW buffer content with Org
formatting (@ref{Links and sorting}).

@item
@strong{Babel and encryption.}  A confirmation function for selective code
block evaluation, a tangle command, and a DWIM command that handles
both decryption and clock-line evaluation (@ref{Babel and encryption}).

@item
@strong{External integration.}  Importing Google Docs via Pandoc, removing
trailing empty headings in automated note directories
(@ref{External integration}).

@item
@strong{Transient menus.}  Quick-access menus for personal projects, Tlon
projects, and @samp{config.org} sections (@ref{Transient menus}).

@item
@strong{Patched functions.}  Upstream Org functions patched via @samp{el-patch} to
improve clock resolution, agenda file handling, and citation insertion
(@ref{Patched functions}).
@end itemize

