@node Agenda file exclusions
@section Agenda file exclusions

@vindex org-extras-agenda-files-excluded
The user option @code{org-extras-agenda-files-excluded} holds a list of file
paths to exclude from Org Agenda generation.  Some files lack the
@samp{property} tag that would normally prevent them from appearing in the
agenda, yet they may still be included if they have been modified
recently (for example, via @code{vulpea-agenda-files-update}).  Adding them
to this list ensures that their TODOs and time logs do not clutter the
agenda view.

The default value is @code{nil} (no files excluded).  The type is a list of
file paths.

@node Automatic ID exclusions
@section Automatic ID exclusions

@vindex org-extras-id-auto-add-excluded-directories
@vindex org-extras-id-auto-add-excluded-files
@vindex org-extras-id-auto-add-excluded-headings
@vindex org-extras-id-auto-add-level-1-dirs
The automatic ID machinery (@ref{ID management}) respects four user
options that control where and how IDs are added.

The user option @code{org-extras-id-auto-add-excluded-directories} is a list
of directory paths.  Files inside these directories will be skipped when
@code{org-extras-id-auto-add-ids-to-headings-in-file} runs.  The default
value is @code{nil}.

The user option @code{org-extras-id-auto-add-excluded-files} is either a list
of file paths to skip, or @code{t} to disable automatic ID addition globally.
Its default value is a list containing @code{paths-file-orb-noter-template}.
When set to a non-nil, non-list value such as @code{t}, the function treats
it as ``exclude all files''.

The user option @code{org-extras-id-auto-add-excluded-headings} is a list of
heading titles (strings) that should never receive an automatic ID@.  The
default value is @samp{("Local variables" "COMMENT Local variables" "TODO
Local variables")}.

The user option @code{org-extras-id-auto-add-level-1-dirs} is a list of
directory paths.  For files in these directories, only level-1 headings
receive automatic IDs, rather than headings at all levels.  The default
value includes the @samp{gptel/} and @samp{chatgpt/} subdirectories under the
notes directory.

@node BBDB anniversaries heading
@section BBDB anniversaries heading

@vindex org-extras-bbdb-anniversaries-heading
The user option @code{org-extras-bbdb-anniversaries-heading} specifies the
Org ID of the heading in @samp{calendar.org} that contains the BBDB
anniversary sexp.  The command @code{org-extras-agenda-toggle-anniversaries}
uses this ID to locate and comment or uncomment the anniversary line
(@ref{Toggling anniversaries}).

The default value is the string
@samp{"2CE5A4E6-842C-4350-ADD0-13D5FC101A20"}.  Set it to @code{nil} to disable
the toggle functionality entirely.

@node Clock report parameters
@section Clock report parameters

@vindex org-extras-clock-report-parameters
The user option @code{org-extras-clock-report-parameters} is a format string
used by @code{org-extras-clock-report-insert} to generate the
@samp{#+BEGIN: clocktable} dynamic block (@ref{Clock reports}).  It
contains two @samp{%s} placeholders: the first for the scope (@samp{agenda},
@samp{file}, or @samp{subtree}), the second for the date range parameters.

The default value is:

@example
#+BEGIN: clocktable :scope %s :maxlevel 9 :narrow 500! :fileskip0 t %s
#+END:
@end example

You might change this to adjust the maximum heading level, column width,
or to add additional clocktable parameters.

@node Participant exclusion regexp
@section Participant exclusion regexp

@vindex org-extras-clock-in-add-participants-exclude
The user option @code{org-extras-clock-in-add-participants-exclude} is a
regexp.  When clocking into a heading whose title matches this regexp,
the automatic participant prompt is suppressed (@ref{Meeting participants}).
This is useful for recurring calendar entries (such as personal focus
blocks) where prompting for participants would be a nuisance.

The default value is @code{nil} (no exclusions).  The type is a regexp
string.

@node Babel evaluation languages
@section Babel evaluation languages

@vindex org-extras-confirm-babel-evaluate-languages
The user option @code{org-extras-confirm-babel-evaluate-languages} is a list
of Org Babel language names (strings) for which code block evaluation
proceeds without confirmation.  The function
@code{org-extras-confirm-babel-evaluate} checks this list and returns
non-nil for languages it contains, which tells Org that no confirmation
prompt is needed (@ref{Babel and encryption}).

The default value is @samp{("emacs-lisp" "python")}.  Add additional
language names (such as @samp{"shell"} or @samp{"ruby"}) if you trust their
evaluation in your workflow.

