@node Link helpers
@section Link helpers

@findex org-extras-link-get-thing-at-point
The function @code{org-extras-link-get-thing-at-point} is the shared
implementation behind the link extraction commands (@ref{Copying URLs and links, , Copying URLs and
links}).  It takes a numeric ARG: 0 for the full bracket link syntax,
1 for the URL, and 2 for the description.  When point is inside an Org
bracket link, it extracts the requested component and adds it to the
kill ring.

@node Heading content helpers
@section Heading content helpers

@findex org-extras-get-heading-contents
The function @code{org-extras-get-heading-contents} returns the body text of
the heading at point as a string, excluding the heading line and any
child subtrees.  If point is before the first heading, it displays a
message and returns @code{nil}.  It uses @code{org-agenda-get-some-entry-text}
with @code{most-positive-fixnum} as the line limit to retrieve the full body
text.

@node Productivity tracking
@section Productivity tracking

@findex org-extras-count-lines-with-expression
@findex org-extras-productivity-of-the-day
The function @code{org-extras-count-lines-with-expression} counts lines in a
string S that match a regexp EXP@.  It is used internally by
@code{org-extras-productivity-of-the-day}.

The function @code{org-extras-productivity-of-the-day} computes how many TODO
lines were added and removed across all agenda files since midnight,
using @samp{git log} to analyze the diffs.  It returns a cons cell of
@samp{(added . removed)} counts.

@node Image filename generation
@section Image filename generation

@findex org-extras-make-image-filename
The function @code{org-extras-make-image-filename} generates a unique
filename for pasted images (@ref{Pasting images from the clipboard}).  It
concatenates @code{paths-dir-org-images}, the current heading's Org ID
(creating one if necessary), and a zero-padded counter suffix (e.g.,
@samp{-001.png}).

@node Capture hook function
@section Capture hook function

@findex org-extras-capture-before-finalize-hook-function
The function @code{org-extras-capture-before-finalize-hook-function} is
designed for @code{org-capture-before-finalize-hook}.  It dispatches on the
capture template key (from @code{org-capture-plist}) and performs
template-specific actions:

@itemize
@item
@samp{"l"}: aligns tags and changes the dictionary to English.
@item
@samp{"la"}: switches to the alternate buffer, adjusts Org Roam tags
(removing ``unprocessed'', ``empty'', etc., adding ``leo''), and inserts a
formatted reference.
@item
@samp{"le"}: similar to @samp{"la"} but inserts a rename reference.
@item
@samp{"s"}: converts an @samp{emacs-slack} link to an external Slack URL@.
@item
@samp{"tmt"}: inserts a web link for the URL on the kill ring.
@item
@samp{"v"}: demotes the captured heading.
@item
@samp{"y"}: downloads a YouTube video from the URL on the kill ring.
@end itemize

@node Clocktable sorting
@section Clocktable sorting

@findex org-extras-clocktable-sorter
The function @code{org-extras-clocktable-sorter} is suitable as a value for
@code{org-clock-clocktable-formatter}.  It sorts clock table entries by
duration in descending order (longest first) before passing them to the
default formatter @code{org-clocktable-write-default}.  The function
signature @samp{(ipos tables params)} matches what the clocktable formatting
machinery expects.

@node Heading navigation
@section Heading navigation

@findex org-extras-goto-beginning-of-heading-text
The function @code{org-extras-goto-beginning-of-heading-text} moves point to
the beginning of the headline text, after the stars, TODO keyword, and
priority cookie (if present).  It uses @code{org-special-ctrl-a/e} to
leverage Org's built-in smart movement and also handles the edge case
where a heading consists of a TODO status followed by a single trailing
space.

@node Subtree display helpers
@section Subtree display helpers

@findex org-extras-show-subtree-hide-drawers
The function @code{org-extras-show-subtree-hide-drawers} hides the entire
subtree, then shows the entry and its children.  This sequence results
in the heading body and child headings being visible while drawers
remain folded.  It is used internally by
@code{org-extras-narrow-to-entry-and-children} (@ref{Narrowing to entries}).

@node Babel evaluation
@section Babel evaluation

@findex org-extras-confirm-babel-evaluate
The function @code{org-extras-confirm-babel-evaluate} is suitable as a value
for @code{org-confirm-babel-evaluate}.  It receives the language name LANG
and returns non-nil when the language is a member of
@code{org-extras-confirm-babel-evaluate-languages} (@ref{Babel evaluation languages, , Babel evaluation
languages}), indicating that no confirmation is needed for that
language.

@node Refiling helpers
@section Refiling helpers

@findex org-extras-refile-at-position
@findex org-extras-refile-to
The function @code{org-extras-refile-at-position} refiles the current subtree
to a specific character POSITION in the current buffer's file.  It calls
@code{org-refile} with a constructed target list.

The function @code{org-extras-refile-to} refiles the current subtree to a
specific HEADING in a given FILE@.  It first finds the heading's position
using @code{org-find-exact-headline-in-buffer} and then calls @code{org-refile}.

@node Linkifying elements
@section Linkifying elements

@findex org-extras-linkify-elements
The function @code{org-extras-linkify-elements} takes a list of STRINGS and
looks up each one in the Org Roam node database.  For strings that match
a node title (case-insensitively), it returns an Org ID link; for
strings with no matching node, it returns the original string unchanged.
The results are joined with SEPARATOR (defaulting to @samp{" . "}).

@node Participant checking
@section Participant checking

@findex org-extras-heading-has-participans-p
The function @code{org-extras-heading-has-participans-p} returns @code{t} if the
current heading already has a line beginning with the participants
introducer string.  It is used by @code{org-extras-clock-in-add-participants}
to avoid adding duplicate participant lines (@ref{Meeting participants}).

@node ID update warning handler
@section ID update warning handler

@findex org-extras--id-update-warning-handler
The function @code{org-extras--id-update-warning-handler} is installed as
advice on @code{display-warning} during @code{org-extras-id-update-id-locations}
(@ref{Updating ID locations}).  When it detects a warning at level
@code{emacs} containing the string ``duplicate IDs found'', it calls
@code{org-extras-id-find-duplicate-ids} to present the duplicates for review.

@node Variables
@chapter Variables

@vindex org-extras-id-auto-add-exclude-file
The buffer-local variable @code{org-extras-id-auto-add-exclude-file}
provides a per-file override for the automatic ID addition machinery
(@ref{Automatic ID addition}).  When set to a non-nil value (typically
via a file-local variable), it prevents
@code{org-extras-id-auto-add-ids-to-headings-in-file} from adding IDs in
that buffer, regardless of other exclusion settings.  The default value
is @code{nil}.

@vindex org-extras-agenda-switch-to-agenda-current-day-timer
The variable @code{org-extras-agenda-switch-to-agenda-current-day-timer}
holds a timer object (or @code{nil}) that can be used to schedule periodic
switches to the current day's agenda view.

@vindex org-extras-particiants-introducer
The constant @code{org-extras-particiants-introducer} holds the string
@samp{"Participants: "} that prefixes the list of meeting participants
inserted by @code{org-extras-add-participants} (@ref{Meeting participants}).

@node Patched functions
@chapter Patched functions

@samp{org-extras.el} uses @samp{el-patch} to modify three upstream Org functions.

@menu
* Clock resolution scope::
* Agenda file checking::
* Citation insertion::
@end menu

@node Clock resolution scope
@section Clock resolution scope

@findex org-resolve-clocks
The function @code{org-resolve-clocks} is patched to use @code{org-agenda-files}
instead of @code{org-files-list} when searching for open clocks to resolve.
This limits the search scope to agenda files rather than all known Org
files, which avoids scanning irrelevant files and reduces the chance of
encountering stale clocks in archived or rarely opened files.

@node Agenda file checking
@section Agenda file checking

@findex org-check-agenda-file
The function @code{org-check-agenda-file} is patched to silently remove
non-existent files from the agenda file list instead of repeatedly
prompting the user.  The upstream version asks ``[R]emove from list or
[A]bort?'' for each missing file, which becomes tedious when multiple
files are missing.

@node Citation insertion
@section Citation insertion

@findex org-cite-insert
The function @code{org-cite-insert} is patched to remove the
@code{org-cite--allowed-p} guard, allowing the command to be invoked in
contexts where citation insertion would normally be disallowed.  This is
useful because even when a citation cannot be inserted, invoking the
command can trigger contextual actions via @samp{embark}.

